service:
  auth: false
  base-path: ''
  endpoints:
    getIntegersWithParameters:
      path: /integers
      method: GET
      docs: Test unformatted integers in query/path parameters using int64 default
      source:
        openapi: ../openapi.yml
      display-name: Get integers with parameters
      request:
        name: GetIntegersRequest
        query-parameters:
          unformattedParam:
            type: optional<long>
            docs: >-
              Query parameter with unformatted integer (should use int64
              default)
          explicitInt32Param:
            type: optional<integer>
            docs: >-
              Query parameter with explicit int32 format (should override
              default)
          explicitInt64Param:
            type: optional<long>
            docs: Query parameter with explicit int64 format (same as default)
          explicitUint32Param:
            type: optional<uint>
            docs: >-
              Query parameter with explicit uint32 format (should override
              default)
          explicitUint64Param:
            type: optional<uint64>
            docs: >-
              Query parameter with explicit uint64 format (should override
              default)
      response:
        docs: Success
        type: IntegerResponse
        status-code: 200
      examples:
        - response:
            body:
              responseInteger: 9223372036854776000
              metadata:
                count: 1000000000000
                maxValue: 9223372036854776000
                minValue: -2147483648
              results:
                - 9223372036854776000
                - 1000000000000
                - 500000000000
    createIntegerResource:
      path: /integers
      method: POST
      docs: Test unformatted integers in request body using int64 default
      source:

      display-name: Create integer resource
      request:

        body:
          properties:

              type: long
              docs: Unformatted integer property (should use int64 default)
            explicitInt32:
              type: integer
              docs: Explicit int32 format (should override default)
            explicitInt64:
              type: long
              docs: Explicit int64 format (same as default)
            explicitUint32:
              type: optional<uint>
              docs: Explicit uint32 format (should override default)
            explicitUint64:
              type: optional<uint64>
              docs: Explicit uint64 format (should override default)
            integerArray:
              type: list<long>
              docs: Array of unformatted integers (should use int64 default)
            mixedFormatArray:
              type: optional<list<IntegerRequestMixedFormatArrayItem>>
              docs: Array with mixed explicit formats
            nestedObject:
              type: optional<IntegerRequestNestedObject>
              docs: Nested object with integer properties
            optionalInteger:
              type: optional<nullable<long>>
              docs: Optional unformatted integer (should use int64 default)
        content-type: application/json
      response:
        docs: Success
        type: IntegerResponse
        status-code: 200
      examples:
        - request:
            unformattedInteger: 9223372036854776000
            explicitInt32: 2147483647
            explicitInt64: 9223372036854776000
            integerArray:
              - 1
              - 2
              - 3
              - 9223372036854776000
          response:
            body:
              responseInteger: 9223372036854776000
              metadata:
                count: 1000000000000
                maxValue: 9223372036854776000
                minValue: -2147483648
              results:
                - 9223372036854776000
                - 1000000000000
                - 500000000000
    getIntegerById:
      path: /integers/{integerId}
      method: GET
      docs: Test unformatted integer in path parameter using int64 default
      source:
        openapi: ../openapi.yml
      display-name: Get integer by ID
      request:
        name: GetIntegersIntegerIdRequest
        path-parameters:
          integerId:
            type: long
            docs: Path parameter with unformatted integer (should use int64 default)
      response:
        docs: Success

            body:
              responseInteger: 9223372036854776000
              metadata:
                count: 1000000000000
